==Chinese==

===Etymology===
From [[柑]] ("large tangerine")  + [[橘]] ("orange").

===Pronunciation===
*Mandarin
**Pinyin: gān jú (gan1 ju2)
*Cantonese
**Jyutping: gam1 gwat1

===Noun===
'''[[柑]][[橘]]''' (simplified and traditional)

# the Cantonese name for [[kumquat]].

====Alternative forms====
*[[金橘]] (Pinyin: ''jīnjú'', literally "golden orange," also pronounced ''gam1 gwat1'' in Cantonese; these characters represent the original name for kumquat, and the spelling used in standard Chinese)

